{"type":"message","id":"565291fc","parentId":"d5d1f920","timestamp":"2026-04-15T02:48:57.104Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current state (02:46 UTC) against the last saved state (02:41 UTC).\n\n**Last state (02:41 UTC):**\n- `cron:6f3323ef` — running (DTLX 5p Monitor) ~5h57m\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — running (QLHV 5p Monitor) — active cycle\n- `cron:e7885813` — running (Agent Status to Lead) — RECOVERED\n- `cron:ac986a8d` — orphaned (~21h+)\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` — running (last msg 02:28 UTC)\n\n\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — running (last delivery 02:11 UTC)\n- `telegram:group:-5168104492` — running, ACTIVE (updated 02:40:45 UTC)\n\nNow checking the current state at 02:46 UTC — the DTLX 5p monitor is still running but it's been running for about 6 hours now, which is longer than expected.\n\nThe QLHV 5p monitor is also still running and is actually this current session itself. The Agent Status cron is running as well. The orphaned cron is still lingering after over 22 hours. The Lead's direct message and QLHV group are both idle, with the group showing its last update from 33 minutes ago at 02:11 UTC. The DTLX ecosystem group is active and still running with the same five child sessions as before, though the last update was 6 minutes ago at 02:40 UTC.\n\nLooking at the bigger picture, the core sessions haven't changed — the monitors are all still running, the orphan is still orphaned, and the group tasks remain active. But the real story is the DTLX ecosystem work: those five child agents spawned in the DTLX ecosystem group have all failed. The three senior-backend subagents are stuck with errors and timeouts, the prompt-optimizer timed out, and the senior-frontend agent is running but hasn't reported any status yet.\n\nThe key difference from the last state is that these child agent failures are now visible — the subagent sessions show their final statuses, which is a real change that needs to be reported. I'm seeing that cron:ac986a8d has been orphaned for over 22 hours, and three of the five child agents in the DTLX ecosystem group have failed or been killed, with only senior-frontend still running. Let me update the state file and send this report.","thinkingSignature":"6e0dc68a8bf993b89a6adbbb8212bab790ad60f1d18e0c828d2c2861351ba58d"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (02:46 UTC) against last saved state (02:41 UTC):\n- The DTLX Ecosystem Group (`telegram:group:-5168104492`) child agents have resolved — all 5 showed final statuses: 3× `failed`/`killed`, 1× `done`, 1× still running (`senior-frontend`)\n- `cron:ac986a8d` is still orphaned (~22h now)\n- All 3 cron monitors still running\n\nThis IS a change — the child agent failures are now observable. Updating state and reporting:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vgqxs0ju2axh_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json","content":"{\n  \"lastChecked\": \"2026-04-15T02:46:00Z\",\n  \"sessions\": {\n    \"cron:6f3323ef\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"DTLX 5p Monitor\", \"startedAt\": \"2026-04-14T20:44:00Z\", \"note\": \"running ~6h 2m — persistent long-running monitor\" },\n    \"cron:ed2d0b5d\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"5p QLHV monitor\", \"startedAt\": \"2026-04-15T02:03:00Z\", \"note\": \"active cycle — current session\" },\n    \"cron:e7885813\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"label\": \"Agent Status to Lead\", \"note\": \"RECOVERED — cycle completed at 02:28 UTC, new cycle running\" },\n    \"cron:ac986a8d\": { \"status\": \"orphaned\", \"label\": \"Telegram send cron\", \"startedAt\": \"2026-04-14T13:04:00Z\", \"note\": \"⚠️ ORPHANED — ~22h stale. Needs kill.\" },\n    \"cron:53c5832a\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"label\": \"Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\", \"note\": \"completed normally ~23:16 UTC Apr 14 — expected\" },\n    \"main\": { \"status\": \"done\", \"no